{"article_id":"dkWtAqbDPs8aUlBc","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"President François Hollande has called on French voters to reject far-right candidate Marine Le Pen","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"and back Emmanuel Macron","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"to succeed him .","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"The pair will face each other in a run-off vote on 7 May","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"after taking the top places in Sunday 's first round ,","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"with Mr Macron the current favourite","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"to win .","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"Mr Hollande said","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"a far-right victory would endanger the country .","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"He said :","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"`` What is at stake is France 's make-up , its unity , its membership of Europe and its place in the world . ''","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"His brief TV address on Monday reflected a move by much of France 's mainstream","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"to line up behind Mr Macron","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"to try to stave off Ms Le Pen .","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"Earlier , defeated candidates , the Republicans ' François Fillon and Socialist Benoît Hamon , both urged supporters to vote for Mr Macron .","depth":5},{"id":15,"text":"Ms Le Pen quickly renewed her attacks on Mr Macron on Monday ,","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"calling him a `` weakling '' for his anti-terrorism policies .","depth":6},{"id":17,"text":"The victory of Ms Le Pen and Mr Macron meant","depth":5},{"id":18,"text":"that , for the first time in six decades , neither of France 's main left-wing or right-wing parties had a candidate remaining in the election .","depth":5},{"id":19,"text":"The pair will hold a TV debate on 3 May ,","depth":5},{"id":20,"text":"aides to Mr Macron said on Monday .","depth":5},{"id":21,"text":"President Hollande said","depth":6},{"id":22,"text":"the far-right would threaten the rupture of Europe ,","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"`` profoundly divide France ''","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"and `` faced with such a risk ,","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"I will vote for Emmanuel Macron '' .","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"He said","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"his former economy minister would `` defend the values","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"which will bring French people together at such an important moment , a serious time for Europe , the world and France '' .","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"But the BBC 's Hugh Schofield in Paris says","depth":5},{"id":30,"text":"the support of Mr Hollande will be a mixed blessing for Mr Macron ,","depth":6},{"id":31,"text":"as it will serve as a reminder to the French people","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"that he was previously a close adviser and minister of the unpopular head of state .","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"Please enable Javascript","depth":3},{"id":34,"text":"to view our poll of polls chart .","depth":3},{"id":35,"text":"About the polling average line","depth":5},{"id":36,"text":"The polling average line looks at the five most recent national polls","depth":6},{"id":37,"text":"and takes the median value ,","depth":8},{"id":38,"text":"ie , the value between the two figures","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"that are higher","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"and two figures","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"that are lower .","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"See individual polls","depth":4},{"id":43,"text":"When he conceded defeat ,","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"the conservative Mr Fillon ,","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"who was third on Sunday with 20 % ,","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"said","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"there was `` no other choice","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"than voting against the far-right '' .","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"However , the position of the fourth-placed candidate , hard-left Jean-Luc Mélenchon ,","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"who took a creditable 19.6 % ,","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"was still unclear .","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"He pointedly refused to back Mr Macron ,","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"whose pro-EU , pro-business and pro-globalisation stance is diametrically opposed to his anti-austerity , eurosceptic approach .","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"Steeve Briois , vice-president of Ms Le Pen 's National Front","depth":14},{"id":55,"text":"( FN ) ,","depth":14},{"id":56,"text":"said","depth":13},{"id":57,"text":"it was hoping to win over Mr Mélenchon 's supporters ,","depth":13},{"id":58,"text":"who he called `` outside the system '' .","depth":13},{"id":59,"text":"`` The voters","depth":15},{"id":60,"text":"who voted for Mr Mélenchon","depth":15},{"id":61,"text":"are angry voters .","depth":14},{"id":62,"text":"They can be in agreement with us , ''","depth":13},{"id":63,"text":"Mr Briois told the Associated Press .","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"However , an IFOP poll on Monday of Mélenchon supporters suggested","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"that 51 % would vote for Mr Macron and only 19 % for Ms Le Pen .","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"Protesters","depth":13},{"id":67,"text":"who burned cars at the Place de la Bastille and Place de la Republique in Paris overnight","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"were chanting","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"`` No Marine and No Macron ! ''","depth":13},{"id":70,"text":"The latest opinion poll , by Opinionway , suggested a second-round victory for Mr Macron by 61 % to 39 % .","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"But there were warnings from Mr Macron 's own party","depth":13},{"id":72,"text":"following a glitzy victory celebration at a Paris bistro","depth":13},{"id":73,"text":"that the job was not yet done .","depth":12},{"id":74,"text":"`` We need to be humble .","depth":13},{"id":75,"text":"The election has n't been won","depth":14},{"id":76,"text":"and we need to bring people together","depth":15},{"id":77,"text":"to win , ''","depth":15},{"id":78,"text":"Richard Ferrand , secretary-general of Mr Macron 's En Marche movement , said .","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"The National Front said","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"that","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"while Mr Macron 's supporters were recovering `` from their showbiz evening '' ,","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"Ms Le Pen was out canvassing in a market in a small northern town .","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"She quickly attacked her rival :","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"`` Mr Macron is a weakling .","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"Here we have a candidate","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"who does n't have a programme","depth":13},{"id":87,"text":"to protect the French people from the threat","depth":14},{"id":88,"text":"posed by Islamist terrorism . ''","depth":14},{"id":89,"text":"She added :","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"`` He is a hysterical , radical 'Europeanist ' .","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"He is for total open borders .","depth":13},{"id":92,"text":"He says","depth":14},{"id":93,"text":"there is no such thing as French culture . ''","depth":14},{"id":94,"text":"The Grand Mosque of Paris called for French Muslims to vote for Mr Macron","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"The police union Alliance","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"( to which Xavier Jugelé ,","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"murdered by a gunman in Paris last Thursday","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"belonged )","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"urged police officers to vote against the FN candidate","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"At 39 , Mr Macron could become the youngest president","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"France has ever had -","depth":8},{"id":102,"text":"and the first president in the Fifth Republic","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"who does not belong to a major party .","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"He secured 8.4 million votes","depth":8},{"id":105,"text":"- more than any other candidate -","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"in the first round .","depth":7},{"id":107,"text":"Mr Macron was Mr Hollande 's economy minister","depth":7},{"id":108,"text":"but quit","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"to create En Marche .","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":"Cut 120,000 public sector jobs","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"and bring down the budget deficit","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"A €50bn","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"( £43bn ; $ 53bn )","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"public investment plan","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"to cover job-training and shift to renewable energy","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"Slash corporation tax from 33 % to 25 %","depth":11},{"id":117,"text":"and let companies renegotiate 35-hour week .","depth":11},{"id":118,"text":"Unify the pension system","depth":11},{"id":119,"text":"Bolster EU ties and the eurozone , higher tariffs","depth":12},{"id":120,"text":"to protect European industry , common border force","depth":12},{"id":121,"text":"In a victory speech to supporters , Mr Macron said :","depth":9},{"id":122,"text":"`` I hope","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"that in a fortnight I will become your president .","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"I want to become the president of all the people of France -","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"the president of the patriots in the face of the threat from the nationalists . ''","depth":11},{"id":126,"text":"Ms Le Pen , 48 , took over the FN leadership from her father in January 2011","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":"and helped her party secure big gains in regional elections .","depth":10},{"id":128,"text":"She won 7.6 million votes on Sunday","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"- the strongest ever result for a FN candidate ,","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"and 2.8 million more than her father , Jean-Marie Le Pen , won for the FN in 2002 .","depth":10},{"id":131,"text":"`` Automatic '' expulsion of illegal immigrants and legal immigration cut to 10,000 per year","depth":7},{"id":132,"text":"Abandon the euro","depth":10},{"id":133,"text":"( and return to the franc ) ,","depth":10},{"id":134,"text":"renegotiate France 's EU membership ,","depth":10},{"id":135,"text":"then hold a `` Frexit '' referendum","depth":10},{"id":136,"text":"Ban wearing of `` ostentatious '' religious symbols such as Muslim headscarves and veils in public . `` Extremist '' mosques closed","depth":9},{"id":137,"text":"and priority to French nationals in social housing","depth":9},{"id":138,"text":"Following the first round results ,","depth":8},{"id":139,"text":"Ms Le Pen made an `` appeal to all patriots '' ,","depth":9},{"id":140,"text":"saying","depth":10},{"id":141,"text":"a vote for her was the key to the `` survival of France '' .","depth":10},{"id":142,"text":"Please include a contact number","depth":9},{"id":143,"text":"if you are willing to speak to a BBC journalist .","depth":9},{"id":144,"text":"You can also contact us in the following ways :","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":289,"left":177,"right":288,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":177,"left":161,"right":176,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":161,"left":151,"right":160,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":151,"left":147,"right":150,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":147,"left":0,"right":146,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":146,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":150,"left":148,"right":149,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":148,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":149,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":160,"left":157,"right":159,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":157,"left":154,"right":156,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":154,"left":152,"right":153,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":152,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":153,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":156,"left":11,"right":155,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":155,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":159,"left":14,"right":158,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":158,"left":15,"right":16,